A group of affiliated investmentfirms led by Bermuda-based Fidelity International Ltd andBoston-based FMR Corp, told the Securities and ExchangeCommission it raised its stake in McGill Manufacturing Co Inc.    The group said it raised its stake to 88,580 shares, or 6.2pct of the total outstanding common stock, after buying 14,135McGill common shares between Jan 19 and March 2 at pricesranging from 33.57 to 34.57 dlrs a share. Reuter&#3;